
Create React App 2.0 has been released today, and it brings a yearâ€™s worth of improvements in a single dependency update.
While React itself doesnâ€™t require any build dependencies, it can be challenging to write a complex app without a fast test runner, a production minifier, and a modular codebase. Since the very first release, the goal of Create React App has been to help you focus on what matters the most â€” your application code â€” and to handle build and testing setup for you.
Many of the tools it relies on have since released new versions containing new features and performance improvements: Babel 7, webpack 4, and Jest 23. However, updating them manually and making them work well together takes a lot of effort. And this is exactly what Create React App 2.0 contributors have been busy with for the past few months: migrating the configuration and dependencies so that you donâ€™t need to do it yourself.
Now that Create React App 2.0 is out of beta, letâ€™s see whatâ€™s new and how you can try it!

